  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ABC Fund TAF Inception phase and component 1</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">During the inception phase we will establish a constructive working relationship with the Fund manager of the ABC Fund  being Bamboo Capital Partners and Injaro Investments. The inception phase will result in the elaboration and approval of a (i) operational manual for the TAF) and (ii) and ME framework for the TAF and the ABC Fund.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFAD and the EU have joined forces to set up the Agri-Business Capital Fund. The ABC Fund&#x2019;s capital structure includes three tranches (A  B and C)  each offering a different risk return profile aimed at attracting various investor classes. An initial capital endowment of US$60 million in grant funding will be contributed by various donors (European Commission (EC)  Luxembourg  and AGRA) as first-loss equity (C-class)  which is expected to leverage around three times the amount in additional funding (A and B class)  or about US$180 million. The Fund design includes a TAF aimed at building the capacity of rural SMEs  Farmer Organizations (FOs) and Financial Intermediaries.
The ABC fund is managed by Bamboo Capital and currently has USD 60 million in committed capital. The fund is meant to serve cooperatives and rural SMEs in mainly Sub-Saharan Africa (later to expand globally) by providing direct investments and smaller investments through local banks. The TAF grant is earmarked to provide technical assistance to cooperatives  rural SME&apos;s and banks that will receive financing from the Agri-Business Capital fund.
The inception phase of the programme will decide (together with the fund manager) operational procedures  workflow  standard documents  TA needs assessment of potential investees  practical TA service delivery  contracting modalities  standardised documentation  the ME framework  etc. 
Managing a grant is a lot of work  and only part of the total grant will be for cooperative development services. But this grant has a lot of potential for us. While the initial grant is only for the first 3 years  the grant is renewable as fund is envisaged to have a fund life of 15 years. In addition  the fund is planned to grow to $ 260M  with the ideal TAF size at 15%-20% of total fund size.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of this project is to get the Technical Assistance Facility (TAF) of the ABC Fund up and running.</narrative>
  </description>
